
[1]honesty

   HON'ESTY, n. on'esty. [L. honestas.]

   1. In principle, an upright disposition; moral rectitude of heart; a
   disposition to conform to justice and correct moral principles, in all
   social transactions. In fact, upright conduct; an actual conformity to
   justice and moral rectitude.

   2. Fairness; candor; truth; as the honesty of a narrative.

   3. Frank sincerity.

       Honesty is chiefly applicable to social transactions, or mutual
                    dealings in the exchange of property.
